@demographics
go-to: menu

**Demographic Groups**

**Industrial Workforce**: The urban working class - DGB union members in steel, coal, chemicals, auto and more remain solidly SPD, while younger and newer workers, especially those in service-adjacent industries, are drifting from the traditional Social-Democratic Party. ~22% of the Population.

**Professional Middle Class**: Small and medium business owners, teachers, engineers and managers make up this category. Consisting of 28% of the population, these are typically swing voters who determine how elections go.

**Welfare & Public Sector**: Nurses, teachers, postal and rail workers, alongside local government employees make up this bloc. They vote mainly for the SPD, organised through the public sector union. ~14% of the Population.

**Business & Capital**: Industrialists in exports, banking, insurance and others make up this demographic. Broadly FDP-aligned and internationalist in their viewpoints. ~10% of the Population.

**Catholic Social Milieu**: Catholic associates, trade unions, church attendees and more. This demographic votes mainly with the CDU & CSU, but economically aligns with the SPD more than the CDU & CSU. ~16% of the Population.

**Activists and Post-Modernists**: Young activists in universities, peace movement veterans, feminists, anti-nuclear campaigners, and emerging ecological activists, voting majority Green, with a minority choosing either the SPD or not to vote at all. ~10% of the Population.

